1. Need to install Node => https://nodejs.org/en/download/ 
2. Need to install git  => https://git-scm.com/downloads
3. Type this in your terminal ( please allocate any of your folder )
   git clone https://github.com/yunoyunoyuno/intern_problem4.git
4. Move to /intern_problem4 directory
5. run npm install.
6. run npm run start
7. In your browser, go to http://localhost:3000
PS.
This is very quick demonstration, doesn't add error handling or using routh handler something like that.
